cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

The paper proposes a framework for improving face recognition performance using deep learning models. The focus is on disentangling appearance and geometry representations, which is a common problem in computer vision and falls under the category of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses the use of spatial transformations to generate geometrically identical faces, which involves techniques related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). Additionally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on challenging datasets, which is a common task in multimedia (cs.MM) and neural networks (cs.NE) research.
